The paper deals with the problem of solving bivariate polynomial systems over the reals, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of signed subresultant sequences suggests a connection to symbolic computation (cs.SC). The algorithms presented also have applications in simultaneous inequalities and real plane algebraic curves, which fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and dynamical systems (cs.DS), respectively.
